   {:e #blake3 "c684933e6e2378a2edf2ac37e0057f93ec1916f88486f9a8cd6f349b298e7d8e" :a :db/ident :v :harvest/session-braid-user-1774362970 :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "c684933e6e2378a2edf2ac37e0057f93ec1916f88486f9a8cd6f349b298e7d8e" :a :harvest/accomplishments :v "Session entity: :recon/trace-eb62bdcbb4d22ad8; Session entity: :recon/trace-7260bd3ba5e2f18f; Session entity: :recon/trace-69e58a079249e2aa; Session entity: :task/t-375f8ad4; Session entity: :recon/trace-19476d63a54e3435; PREMORTEM-RISK-2: Concurrent daemon + direct writer. If daemon is running and another process writes txn files directly, daemon must detect and apply them. Already solved by LiveStore.refresh_if_needed() (INV-DAEMON-002). Risk: refresh not called before dispatch. Mitigation: refresh is the FIRST action in the request handler, unconditionally.; Session entity: :recon/trace-eb8e72bc52194a84; Session entity: :task/t-9fbf72fc; Session entity: :recon/trace-97f76aa8601da145; Session entity: :recon/trace-93574c47a271fb21; DAEMON-ARCH-1: MCP Protocol Reuse Architecture. The daemon reuses the EXACT JSON-RPC protocol and tool dispatch from mcp.rs (1,731 LOC). The call_tool() function (mcp.rs:319-344) dispatches to 11 tool handlers. These handlers must be made pub(crate) so daemon.rs can call them. The daemon IS the MCP server with a different transport layer (Unix socket at .braid/daemon.sock instead of stdin/stdout). This means daemon.rs contains ONLY: (1) lifecycle management (start/stop/lock/signal), (2) socket accept loop, (3) runtime datom emission wrapper, (4) connection management. All tool logic stays in mcp.rs. The handle_tools_call function (mcp.rs:1131-1156) with its guidance footer injection (append_guidance_footer, mcp.rs:1167-1201) is shared between MCP stdio mode and daemon socket mode. Verification: after extraction, existing MCP tests (expected_tool_count, tool_names_match_expected_set, tool_descriptions_quality) must continue to pass unchanged. ADR-DAEMON-002.; Session entity: :recon/trace-a3c9b323710fe8bf; Session entity: :task/t-dd3ec886; Session entity: :task/t-00a1f205; Session entity: :recon/trace-2eb6b23d3931cbee; DAEMON-ARCH-6: CLI Auto-Routing. In main.rs, before executing any command via the existing run() dispatch, check for daemon availability. Algorithm: (1) Resolve store path from command. (2) Let sock_path = store_path.join('daemon.sock'). (3) If sock_path.exists() { attempt UnixStream::connect(sock_path) with 2s timeout }. (4) If connection succeeds: serialize command as JSON-RPC tools/call message, write to socket, read response, parse, return. (5) If connection fails (ConnectError, Timeout, or any IO error): fall back to direct mode silently (eprintln in verbose mode only). The JSON-RPC serialization maps CLI commands to tool names: status→braid_status, query→braid_query, observe→braid_observe, etc. Commands that don't have MCP equivalents (init, merge, daemon) are always direct-mode. INV-DAEMON-007, INV-DAEMON-004.; Session entity: :recon/trace-7855f156ead89daf; Unix Socket Transport for Daemon; Session entity: :recon/trace-462dce2ee0774450; Session entity: :task/t-03561cf0; Session entity: :recon/trace-38ef496551ccda91; Session entity: :recon/trace-d14ccd59b59ae465; Session entity: :recon/trace-0cd81b6d774a7fc0; Session entity: :task/t-e3d271c3; Session entity: :recon/trace-11c5fd234d731b3c; Session entity: :task/t-0c9c8e74; Session entity: :recon/trace-02b5d36b69bb0346; PREMORTEM-RISK-1: Stale lock after crash. If daemon is SIGKILL'd, .braid/daemon.lock remains with dead PID. Mitigation: kill(pid, 0) check on startup (INV-DAEMON-005). Test: start daemon, kill -9, verify next start succeeds after stale-lock cleanup.; Session entity: :task/t-88e63098; Session entity: :recon/trace-34465740e578e484; Session entity: :task/t-a2dd8b78; Session entity: :recon/trace-9bbc62148ea7e57a; Session entity: :task/t-18bdbe69; DAEMON-ARCH-7: DaemonError Enum Design. Caller-distinguishable error variants for all daemon failure modes: LockHeld { pid: u32 } — another daemon is running (INV-DAEMON-001). LockStale { pid: u32 } — lock exists but process is dead (INV-DAEMON-005, recovered automatically). BindFailed(io::Error) — cannot bind socket (permissions, path too long, socket in use). AlreadyStopping — shutdown already in progress. NotRunning — stop/status requested but no daemon. ConnectionFailed(io::Error) — client cannot connect to daemon socket. Timeout — client connection or read timeout exceeded. StoreError(BraidError) — underlying store operation failed. ProtocolError(String) — malformed JSON-RPC or invalid method. Each variant maps to a structured error response with what/why/fix/spec_ref following INV-INTERFACE-009 pattern from error.rs. DaemonError implements Display, Error, and From<BraidError> + From<io::Error>.; Session entity: :recon/trace-c13f71a436030b2d; Session entity: :recon/trace-ab0250432af1489f; PREMORTEM-RISK-5: Fallback split-brain. CLI detects no daemon, falls back to direct mode, writes datoms. Meanwhile daemon starts. Now daemon's cached hashes are stale. Mitigation: daemon startup always does a full refresh_if_needed() before accepting connections. Race window is negligible (startup serialized by lock acquisition).; Session entity: :task/t-8e3120b9; Session entity: :recon/trace-c3b5188d6680f308; PREMORTEM-RISK-3: Socket exhaustion / leaked connections. If clients connect but never close, file descriptors accumulate. Mitigation: per-connection timeout (30s), max concurrent connections limit (16), connection cleanup on read error or timeout.; Session entity: :task/t-31c403c4; DAEMON-ARCH-10: Protocol Typestate and Error Handling. Wire protocol: newline-delimited JSON-RPC 2.0 over Unix socket (identical to MCP). Error codes: -32700 parse error, -32600 invalid request, -32601 method not found, -32602 invalid params, -32603 internal error, -32000 store error, -32001 daemon shutting down. Daemon-specific methods beyond tools/call: daemon/shutdown (graceful stop), daemon/status (health check returning PID, uptime, request_count, datom_count). Request IDs: integer or string from client, echoed in response, stored in :runtime/request-id. Idempotency: reads are idempotent, writes are idempotent by content addressing (same datoms → same txn file hash). Buffer limit: 1MB per request line. Connection timeout: 30s idle. Partial write handling: atomic line writes (small JSON responses fit in pipe buffer). Client disconnect during processing: continue to completion, emit runtime datom, response lost (acceptable). INV-DAEMON-004.; Session entity: :task/t-75b74878; Session entity: :recon/trace-5ba34b03e5d261ee; DAEMON-ARCH-8: CLI Command Surface. Three new CLI commands under 'braid daemon' subcommand: (1) 'braid daemon start [--foreground]' — acquire lock, open LiveStore, install runtime schema, bind socket, enter accept loop. --foreground keeps process in terminal (MVP: foreground-only, daemonize deferred). (2) 'braid daemon stop' — connect to daemon socket, send JSON-RPC method 'daemon/shutdown', wait for clean exit confirmation, verify lock+socket removed. If daemon unresponsive: print PID for manual kill. (3) 'braid daemon status' — check lock file existence and PID validity. If running: connect to socket, send 'daemon/status' method, print PID, uptime, request count, store datom count. If not running: print 'daemon not running'. CLI parsing: add DaemonCommand enum to commands/mod.rs, DaemonAction subcommand enum with Start { foreground: bool }, Stop, Status variants. Wire into Command enum and run() dispatch.; Session entity: :recon/trace-cc66d4e2d31ecf84; Reuse MCP Protocol for Daemon; Session entity: :task/t-6f7280a2; Runtime Schema as Store Datoms; Session entity: :recon/trace-535df597f5d0b2c4; Session entity: :recon/trace-bb4e4689b6031522; Session entity: :recon/trace-c063a3e42d63d2ec; Session entity: :task/t-df9a11cf; Session entity: :recon/trace-8b8063517e58374e; Session entity: :task/t-6bb54b85; Session entity: :recon/trace-26988510d0fa3dd8; Session entity: :recon/trace-94f3c873b858a6e3; Session 041 started: PERF-4 Introspective Observer Daemon constitutional research/spec memo. Goal: produce complete design memo before implementation, manage all knowledge in braid.; Session entity: :task/t-b57a4fb9; Session entity: :recon/trace-807c1cd7f6aeb1e7; Session entity: :recon/trace-0fcc804bc1f6d9c4; Session entity: :recon/trace-8f6ad706f927c8ce; DAEMON-ARCH-3: Lock File Protocol. Lock file at .braid/daemon.lock. Contents: PID as ASCII text (e.g., '12345'). Creation: O_CREAT|O_EXCL for atomicity (two processes racing both try exclusive create, only one succeeds). Stale detection: on startup, if lock exists, read PID, call kill(pid, 0). If ESRCH (process dead), remove stale lock and re-acquire. If process alive, return DaemonError::LockHeld { pid }. Release: on clean shutdown, remove lock file AFTER flushing LiveStore and removing socket file. Crash path: lock remains with dead PID, recovered on next startup. INV-DAEMON-001, INV-DAEMON-005.; Session entity: :recon/trace-493fd1eeb4c635e4; Session entity: :task/t-e709cceb; Session entity: :task/t-37a56838; Session entity: :recon/trace-4a7d5284f0e88136; Session entity: :recon/trace-76f566c4f600bad2; Session entity: :recon/trace-0f8c2a5336911e60; DAEMON-ARCH-2: Runtime Schema Design. Six new schema attributes for reflexive observation: :runtime/command (String, One) — command name or tool name. :runtime/request-id (String, One) — JSON-RPC request id as string. :runtime/latency-ms (Long, One) — wall clock milliseconds for request processing. :runtime/outcome (String, One) — 'success' or 'error'. :runtime/datom-count (Long, One) — store.len() at request start (for tracking growth). :runtime/cache-hit (Boolean, One) — whether refresh_if_needed() found no new txns (O(1) fast path). These attributes are installed as schema datoms during daemon startup via a runtime schema transaction. They follow C3 (schema-as-data) and are queryable via standard Datalog: [:find ?cmd ?lat :where [?e :runtime/command ?cmd] [?e :runtime/latency-ms ?lat]]. Each command execution creates one runtime entity with all 6 attributes plus :db/ident (:runtime/req-{hash}). Runtime datoms use the same 6 ADR-029 lifecycle attributes as all other knowledge. ADR-DAEMON-003, INV-DAEMON-003.; Session entity: :recon/trace-9dc342ebe9f303e6; Session 041 — PERF-4 Constitutional Memo + Task Crystallization Complete. Created: 14 spec elements (3 ADRs + 9 INVs + 2 NEGs in DAEMON namespace), 10 architectural observations, 2 test observations, 5 premortem risks. Task hierarchy: 1 EPIC (t-8f71bbb2), 8 implementation tasks (D4-1..8), 4 test tasks (D4-TEST-1..4), 23 dependency edges. 16 auto-generated COTX tasks closed as superseded. 7 pre-existing tasks linked as future work (PERF-4a, PERF-4b, DOGFOOD-REFLEXIVE, WALPHA-1, ROUTING-INCR-1, BLANKET-DYNAMICS-1). Dependency graph validated: D4-1 and D4-3 are entry points (no deps), TEST-4 is the terminal node (depends on everything). No implementation code written — session was spec-first per constitutional requirement. Store: 78160 datoms (+2264 this session), 16 new tasks.; DAEMON-ARCH-5: Runtime Datom Emission Wrapper. handle_with_observation(live, request) wraps EVERY tool dispatch. Pattern: (1) Record start = Instant::now(). (2) Record datom_count_before = live.store().len(). (3) Record cache_hit = live.refresh_if_needed() returns false (no new txns). (4) Dispatch: result = handle_tools_call(id, params, live). (5) Record elapsed_ms = start.elapsed().as_millis(). (6) Record outcome = if result has error field then 'error' else 'success'. (7) Create runtime entity :runtime/req-{blake3(request_id + timestamp)[..16]}. (8) Build 6 datoms: command, request-id, latency-ms, outcome, datom-count, cache-hit. (9) write_tx(runtime_tx). Best-effort: if runtime datom write fails, do NOT fail the original request. Log to stderr. (10) Return original result. This wrapper MUST be applied on BOTH success and error paths (INV-DAEMON-008). The wrapper is the finally-pattern: timing starts before dispatch, datom emission happens after dispatch regardless of outcome.; Session entity: :recon/trace-de871fbad84cf468; Session entity: :task/t-5d248510; Session entity: :recon/trace-f54c9363858ea568; Session entity: :recon/trace-96e976175d73d279; Session entity: :task/t-8f71bbb2; PREMORTEM-RISK-4: Runtime datoms lost on error paths. If the error handling bypasses datom emission, INV-DAEMON-008 is violated. Mitigation: runtime datom emission wraps the ENTIRE handler as a finally/defer pattern — measure start time before dispatch, emit datom after dispatch regardless of outcome.; DAEMON-ARCH-9: State Machine Formalization. Daemon lifecycle: 5 states (NotRunning, Starting, Running, Stopping, Failed), 6 transitions. Request lifecycle per connection: 6 states (Idle, ReadingRequest, Validating, Processing, EmittingRuntimeDatoms, Responding). Key invariants per state: Running requires valid lock + bound socket + consistent LiveStore. Stopping requires no new connections + in-flight completing. Auto-start/stop DEFERRED to future session (adds complexity without validating core hypothesis). Concurrency: all request processing is globally serialized (single-threaded MVP). Multiple connections may be in Idle simultaneously but only one processes at a time. refresh_if_needed() is the FIRST action in every request dispatch, unconditionally. This is formally the barrier that maintains INV-DAEMON-002.; Session entity: :task/t-7e1b2bf1; DAEMON-TEST-1: Comprehensive Test Strategy. Four test tiers: TIER 1 (Unit): test_acquire_lock_success, test_acquire_lock_already_held, test_stale_lock_recovery, test_release_lock_cleanup, test_runtime_schema_installed, test_daemon_error_variants, test_parse_jsonrpc_request, test_handle_with_observation_success, test_handle_with_observation_error. TIER 2 (Integration): test_daemon_start_stop (full lifecycle), test_daemon_status_query (braid_status via socket), test_external_write_visible (INV-DAEMON-002), test_daemon_direct_equivalence (INV-DAEMON-004), test_connection_timeout (PM-3). TIER 3 (Property/proptest): proptest_runtime_datom_completeness (N commands → N runtime entities), proptest_external_write_visibility (any sequence of external writes visible after refresh), proptest_daemon_direct_equivalence (any command + store state produces same result via daemon or direct). TIER 4 (E2E): scripts/e2e_daemon.sh — start daemon, run 5 commands, verify runtime datoms, verify daemon-direct equivalence, clean shutdown, verify no leftover files.; Session entity: :task/t-6e6dde06; Session entity: :recon/trace-33f22918470275e8; Session entity: :task/t-39b20a3f; DAEMON-ARCH-4: Socket Server Architecture. Unix socket at .braid/daemon.sock. Single-threaded accept loop (no tokio/async for MVP). Per-connection flow: accept → read lines → parse JSON-RPC → refresh_if_needed() → dispatch via call_tool() → emit runtime datoms → write response → loop. Connection timeout: 30s idle. Max concurrent connections: 16 (accept but queue beyond 1 active). Newline-delimited JSON-RPC 2.0 — identical wire format to MCP stdio. Daemon owns sole LiveStore instance. &mut passed to handlers enforcing exclusivity. Signal handling: SIGTERM/SIGINT set AtomicBool shutdown flag. Accept loop checks flag each iteration. On shutdown: stop accepting, complete in-flight, flush LiveStore, remove socket file, remove lock file, exit 0. INV-DAEMON-006, ADR-DAEMON-001.\nDaemon-Direct Semantic Equivalence; No Unsynchronized Mutation Paths; Session entity: :task/t-8da815d1; Reflexive Runtime Datom Emission; No Speculative Daemon Features; Graceful Shutdown Safety; Session entity: :task/t-29b48cc5; Session entity: :task/t-b0c36992; No Parallel Observability Stack; Session entity: :task/t-79103fb0; Session entity: :task/t-4753c96e; Runtime Datom Completeness on Error Paths; CLI Auto-Routing; Daemon Store Consistency; Session entity: :task/t-015b9c02; Lock File PID Correctness; Session entity: :task/t-8fa0a027; Single Daemon Per Directory; Session entity: :task/t-97707ab5" :op :assert}
